<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="saying-n">saying <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'seɪɪŋ/    美 /'seɪɪŋ/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>(说) 话；(发表) 言论：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>sayings and doings 
言行</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>格言；警句；谚语：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a collection of the sayings of great men 
伟人名言集</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="as-the-saying-is-goes">as the saying is / goes</h3>
<p>1.<strong>常言道：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>“Practice makes perfect,” as the saying goes.
常言道：“熟能生巧。”</p><footer>2015 四川书面表达</footer></div>

<h3 id="go-without-saying">go without saying</h3>
<p>1.<strong>不言而喻：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It goes without saying that the proposal will be accepted. 
这项建议将被采纳，这是不言而喻的。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>“You can’t judge a book by its cover,” <strong><em>_</em></strong>_.  （2013 全国）<br />
A.as the saying goes old<br />
B.goes as the old saying<br />
C.as the old saying goes<br />
D.goes as old the saying  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. C  </p></div>